Up stair we watched the sum of all fears, then the rookie.  Downstairs we watched a walk to remember, and the count of monte cristo.  I watched the sum of all fears and the count of monte cristo.  Then this morning, at church, my parents became members of Village 7 Presbyterian church, which is a part of PCA (presbyterian church of america).  So yeah that was fun.  Then in Sunday school (we only have like 8 kids in our class) we got a new teacher.  He is 18, a high school senior, and sooooo HOT!!  *wow* ok I'm done.
